title: Unemployment rate in Canada 2024
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 11 data points. The chart has 3 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely positive which exists from 2024 to 2019.
Similarly, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2019 to 2016.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2016 to 2014.
gold: The statistic shows the unemployment rate in Canada from 2014 to 2018 , with projections up until 2024 . In 2018 , the unemployment rate in Canada was at around 5.83 percent . Canada 's economy Three-quarter of Canada 's workforce is employed in the services sector , with the other two sectors , agriculture and industry , accounting for the rest of Canada 's employment .
